707921f-b.title: Manhattan: 2nd Avenue - 76th Street (East)
707921f-b.text:
(1)
Second Ave., east side, north from and including East 76th Street, showing the pushcart market that extends for many blocks. Note the display of merchandise on the sidewalk and from the store fronts.
December 28, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, farther northward.
December 28, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

714471f-a.title: Manhattan: 76th Street (East) - 2nd Avenue
714471f-a.text:
235-225 East 76th Street, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Second Avenue. The Cornell Memorial M. E. Church and Chapel, No. 233231, is just west of Second Avenue. These buildings will be demolished
shortly to make way for an apartment house.
January 27, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
